<p><strong>Introduction</strong></p>
<p>Sedra/Smith's Microelectronic Circuits, now in its 7th edition, is widely considered the definitive textbook for undergraduate and graduate courses in microelectronics. This comprehensive textbook provides a deep understanding of the fundamental principles of microelectronic circuits, from basic semiconductor physics to advanced circuit analysis techniques. The 7th edition features a wealth of new material, including expanded coverage of modern semiconductor devices and circuit design techniques.</p>
